text: providing a positive experience for
today's customers can be an uphill
battle surging contact volumes agent
burnout and increasing customer
expectations AWS agent assist and
conversational analytics Solutions
powered by generative AI let you improve
operational efficiency in your contact
center without sacrificing customer
satisfaction we combine automated call
transcription with natural language
processing and Foundation models to
derive actionable insights into customer
conversations and agent performance so
how does this apply to customer service
agents generative AI can assist agents
by automating notetaking recommending
real-time responses for quick accurate
problem solving and providing concise
summaries for
calls thanks for calling wheels for rent
my name is Alex whom do I have the
pleasure of speaking with today thanks
Alex my name is Carla I'm supposed to
pick up my rental car in 2 hours but I
need to cancel will I be charged the
cancellation
nice to meet you Carla let me check you
will receive a full refund minus a
cancellation fee of $100 agent assist
draws on a library of FAQs and trusted
knowledge sources to generate the best
responses for your agents in real time
whether it's helping cut ramp up time
for new agents or ensuring experienced
agents have answers at their fingertips
by having a human in the loop the risk
of delivering incorrect statements is
minimized once the call finishes
generative AI can analyze the
conversation transcript and
automatically produce a summary
including the issue and outcome of the
call this can reduce the time agents and
managers spend taking or reviewing notes
the summary also provides relevant key
points when transferring contacts to
ensure a smooth customer Journey
furthermore conversational analytics and
quality management can be powered by
generative AI to review contacts and
automatically populate scorecards
answering questions like did the
customer leave the call satisfied as
part of a pre-filled evaluation form
along with rationale for each agent
coaching or training opportunities can
also be identified to further improve
operations it can also be used by
supervisors and managers to analyze
customer sentiment identify high
frequency issues and gain new insights
at the aggregate level or by diving deep
into the details of individual calls
